How to make a virtual environment:

First: sudo apt-get install python3-pip
Second:sudo pip3 install virtualenv 
Third: virtualenv -p /usr/bin/python2.7 venv(use this ONLY of Python2)
OR
Fourth: virtualenv -p python3 venv OR python3 -m venv myenv
Fifth: ENTER Using -- . venv/bin/activate 
Sixth: EXIT using -- deactivate


How to clon:

1. Go to terminal 
2. type: git clone then use HTTPS link next to clone
3. enter and done 

Git Push/Pull:

1. git status  
2. git add _____________ (name the files)
3. git commit (add comment)
4. git status 
5. git push 

How to creat a server when doing HTML:

Tto run this go to terminal and type python -m http.server (just works with python 3) then open browser type localhost:(with the number the port is) For example: localhost:8000

Terminal navigation:

cd .. - go back once
cd ~ - go back to home 
pwd - know the path your on
cd (file name) - when entering a directory 
mkdir (name of file) -  make a directory
rm -fr - remove a directory
gvim (file name)- enter a file to change or write
cat (file name) - view what is in file without opening 

GVIM:
:w - save 
:q - exit 
i - insert 
esc - escape insert 
L - Right
H - Left
K - Up
J - Down
:set number - put numbers 
:colorscheme (name of desiree color) examples::desert or any other

